      "messageBody": "The root .gitignore line 42 has `lib/` from the standard Python build-\nartifact list. That pattern was too broad — it also caught apps/web/lib/,\nsilently dropping the TypeScript modules every new page imports\n(@/lib/company-os/*, @/lib/sales-machine/*, @/lib/sales-automation/*,\n@/lib/generated/*).\n\nTwo CI jobs failed on PR #713 because of this:\n- \"Next.js web verify\" — typecheck reported TS2307 for every @/lib/* import\n  even though apps/web/tsconfig.json defines the alias correctly.\n- \"verify\" (verify_client_acquisition_delivery_os.py) — reported\n  MISSING apps/web/lib/company-os/company-os.ts.\n\nFix: add `!apps/web/lib/` and `!apps/web/lib/**` immediately after the\nPython `lib/` rule so it un-ignores only the web app's lib directory and\nleaves the Python build pattern intact everywhere else.\n\nThis commit also adds the six previously-ignored TypeScript files that\nthe new pages depend on:\n- apps/web/lib/analytics/events.ts\n- apps/web/lib/company-os/company-os.ts\n- apps/web/lib/company-os/pipeline.ts\n- apps/web/lib/generated/founder-dashboard.ts\n- apps/web/lib/sales-automation/lead-sources.ts\n- apps/web/lib/sales-machine/ultimate-sales-os.ts\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01CiamJCEcmQ9RQUTk7BHtst",
      "messageHeadline": "fix(gitignore): scope Python lib/ pattern so apps/web/lib/ lands",
      "oid": "c74c7030a198a90eceaef8a3fb92f0ae72c728f7"
    },
